<L>__{exterior of cabin night}
<A>__{rocklin is headed for the corral as dave catches up to him.}
<C>__{dave}
<P>__{(glancing back to the cabin)}
<D>__{fer a man who's got a despise fer wimmin, you sure do get all snaggled up with 'em.}
<L>__{interior of cabin night}
<A>__{arly, her back to us, is standing in the open doorway watching the two headed for the corral. her mood is evidenced by the manner in which she suddenly slams shut the door. as she turns and leans against it, we see tears in her eyes, and hear suppressed sobs. her eyes light on the bits of torn letter, and presently we see her face set itself grimly, and now she walks toward the fireplace and, passing the torn bite of paper, kicks at them viciously.}
